Source: pg-query-rewrite
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/pierreforstmann/pg_query_rewrite

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-query-rewrite
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-query-rewrite
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Rewrite SQL statements with a PostgreSQL ProcessUtility hook
 pg_query_rewrite translates matching SQL statements to predefined target SQL
 through a ProcessUtility hook. It must be loaded via
 shared_preload_libraries before CREATE EXTENSION is run in each database that
 should use the rewrite rules.
